# Quality Gates

## Before Commit

- [ ] Tests written and passing (pytest)
- [ ] Code formatted correctly (4 spaces, ruff format)
- [ ] No hardcoded configuration/secrets
- [ ] Error handling for external calls (API, file I/O)
- [ ] Logging for library code (not print)

## Before Merge

- [ ] All quality checks passing (ruff check, ruff format, pytest)
- [ ] Test coverage maintained where applicable
- [ ] Documentation updated for public APIs

## Code Quality Metrics

| Metric | Threshold |
|--------|-----------|
| Function length | ≤ 20 lines |
| File size | ≤ 250 lines |
| Cyclomatic complexity | ≤ 10 |
| Test coverage | ≥ 80% (for critical paths) |

## Testing Requirements

- Write tests before implementation (TDD)
- Unit tests for business logic
- Test error paths, not just happy paths

```python
def test_valid_login():
    user = User("test@example.com", "hashed_password")
    with patch("user_repository.find_by_email", return_value=user):
        result = user_service.login("test@example.com", "password")
    assert result.is_success is True
```

## Security Checks

- No hardcoded API keys, passwords, or tokens
- Use environment variables for configuration
- Validate all user inputs
